	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories An eight-year-old boy drowned while swimming in the Mzamba
lagoon near the Wild Coast Sun, Port Edward, on Saturday afternoon. The National Sea Rescue Institute was activated after
lifeguards reported a drowning in the lagoon. Police search and rescue divers and NSRI rescue swimmers searched
the water while the NSRI jet ski was also deployed, NSRI Port Edward Station
Commander John Nicholas said in a statement. "During an extensive search operation police search and
rescue divers located and recovered the body of the child from the water and
sadly the child...[had] been declared deceased by paramedics." Police have opened an inquest docket. "Condolences are conveyed to family and police are
assisting the family," Nicholas said. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  